    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level for a Model Risk Level 3, Medium assurance assessment. The single below-requirement factor (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) is mitigated by the direct equivalence of the ASTM F1717 protocol to the COU loading scenario and the consistency of results across two independent laboratories. The overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support the regulatory submission claim that the FEA framework accurately predicts compression-bending performance of the non-cannulated pedicle screw construct within the stated acceptance bounds.",
